reviewText: This DVD has good information about the history of motorcycles with lots of little facts about Harley Davidson and Indian motorcycles. It is well filmed and is entertaining.

There was an episode of Modern Marvels: Motorcycles which aired on November 15, 1999 (Season 6, Ep. 43) with a run time of 2 hours.  I have it on VHS and I have just about worn out the tape watching it.  I wanted to replace my VHS version with a DVD, so I bought this.  VERY DISAPPOINTED!  This is not the same episode.  This is either an abbreviated version (50 minutes) with all the interesting parts cut out or a different episode entirely.  Wish I could find a DVD of the Modern Marvels: Motorcycles which aired 11/15/99 (Season 6, Ep 43).
Interesting history and sicence of motorcycles
It's an interesting documentary, but thought they could have added more about the bikes mechanically and technically.
It was a great movie starting from the early days to now.and it didn't just talk about harley davidson.it was great fun to watch I recommend it
It was interesting to see for any motorcycle enthusiast. History Channel is always on the outside looking in, on all their shows, but worth a look.
It was a gift....he loves it....
Very informative.  We enjoy many of the history channel's programs.  We would definitely recommend this.
